# load modules
import re
import pprint
import pandas as pd

# load local scripts
from dm_association_analysis import create_candidates
from dm_association_analysis import support_prune
from dm_association_analysis import apriori
from dm_association_analysis import generate_rules


# load look up table for the product IDs
idDic = dict() 
with open('bakery/products.csv', 'r') as f:
    for line in f:
        line_parts = line.strip().split(',')
        idDic[line_parts[0]] = line_parts[1]
        
#
# Processing all the files
#

dataset = [] # list of transactions

infile_dic = dict() # A dictionary of the input files (when using loops)
infile_dic['infile_1k']  = 'bakery/1000/1000-out1.csv'
infile_dic['infile_5k']  = 'bakery/5000/5000-out1.csv'
infile_dic['infile_20k'] = 'bakery/20000/20000-out1.csv'
infile_dic['infile_75k'] = 'bakery/75000/75000-out1.csv'

inFilePath = infile_dic['infile_1k']
infile = open(inFilePath,'r') 
for line in infile :
    line_parts = re.split(r',\s',line.rstrip('\n\r'))
    dataset.append([idDic[x] for x in line_parts[1:]])

D = map(set, dataset)
#pprint.pprint (dataset[:4])

# Generate candidate itemsets.
C1 = create_candidates(dataset, verbose=True) # candidate 1-itemsets
print size(C1)
